{% extends "base.jinja" %}
{% block title %}Projects{% endblock %}
{% block logo %}PROJECTS{% endblock %}
{% block content %}
    <div class="article">
        <h1 class="center-text">Bandit</h1>
        <img src="/bandit.png" class="project-display" align="left" />
        <p>Web crawler application framework. Users can create single/multi node data pipelines. Features automatic scaling, customizable deployments, and observability.</p>
        <p>Originally designed to crawl tor hidden services, later expanded to extract and process a diverse array of OSINT sources.
        <p>Source code is proprietary. For sales inquiries, please contact me via LinkedIn.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="article">
        <h1 class="center-text"><a href="//informe.cloud">Informe</a></h1>
        <img src="/informe.png" class="project-display" align="left" />
        <p>Analyzes current events from various sources on the web. Users can create customized news dashboards using JSON configuration. Feeds can be filtered via features such as sentiment, geography, and ticker symbol. Data can be visualized via text feed, map, or sentiment graph.</p>
        <p>Data feeds are generated by the Bandit web crawler.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="article">
        <h1 class="center-text">Artemis</h1>
        <img src="/artemis.png" class="project-display" align="left" />
        <p>Play games in real life with your friends using maps on your mobile device! Development still in-progress, expected to release in early 2022.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="article">
        <h1 class="center-text"><a href="https://anigraph.s3-us-west-1.amazonaws.com/index.html">Anigraph</a></h1>
        <img src="/anigraph.png" class="project-display" align="left" />
        <p>Displays the similarity of popular anime in the form of a directed graph. Built using data mining features from the Bandit web crawler.</p>
        <p>Updated infrequently.</p>
    </div>
{% endblock %}
